insert into events values(2134747,10018,'2016/04/19','29 La Playa St','Monterey' ,'CA','93940','images/content/dating1.png','Beaches','If you love beaches like I do, come! We can play volleyball or simply relax and people watch.','Theres something magical about the Monterey Bay, whether youre strolling the beach with your kids or soulmate or just watching the sun set over the water. Monterey County offers 99 miles of beautiful beaches across the pacific coastline, many of which are home to some of the best surf breaks along the West Coast. Moderate ocean temperatures and year-around sunshine make a day at the beach more enjoyable. Discover beaches perfect for any occasion, whether for a dog walk, a volleyball play or to simply relax and people watc','dating','MyTreat','#beach');
insert into events values(2134757,10019,'2016/04/20','815 Cole St','SF','CA','94117','images/content/dating2.png','Ice cream','This Ice Cream is My datey! Looking for ice cream LOVERS!','One of My favorite bar andrestaurant mashups combines a 1930s ice cream parlor think handmade malts, ice cream, shakes,upscale diner treats with craft cocktails modern flavors, making this the perfect place to woo your chosen one Jimmy Stewartstyle. Boozy malts and milkshakes change with the season and theyÕve got sexy booze desserts on the menu, like the This Drink Is My Datey Allagash Curieux bourbon-barrel aged ale over butterscotch, milk chocolate, and banana puddinÕ ice creams, with caramelized banana, whipped cream, and a cherry,or the Pink Violet, a sweet vanilla and violetflavored soda that changes color from blue to pink itÕs being made.','dating','Split','#ice cream');
insert into events values(2134767,10020,'2016/04/21','886 Cannery Row','Monterey','CA','93940','images/content/dating3.png','Open sea','Do you enjoy tuna and sharks speed past, sardines swarm in huge, glittering schools, and sea turtles swim lazily across the 90-foot window Come to the best aquarium of the bay area','Out to sea and on the goÑlifes in constant motion in the open ocean. The Monterey Aquarium is a place where tuna and sharks speed past, sardines swarm in huge, glittering schools, and sea turtles swim lazily across the 90-foot window. Nearby, colorful puffins await their next meal, and brilliant jellies pulse through the water.','dating','MyTreat','#sea');
